      "translation": "The pandemic's principal impact on our 2020 financial performance was on new business sales, as containment measures across our numerous markets restricted face-to-face sales activities, particularly in the first half of 2020. Despite new business value of US$2.765 billion in 2020 representing a 33% decrease compared to 2019, we rapidly adopted new digital tools, and the widespread relaxation of movement restrictions supported a recovery in sales momentum. AIA China contributed the most to the Group's new business value in 2020 and was also our first reporting segment to demonstrate a recovery in sales momentum, as that region progressively eased strict lockdown measures from March 2020 onwards."
